  "status": "Review",
  "summary": "This proposal is a security token standard that extends [ERC-1155](./eip-1155.md) to provide a flexible framework for managing compliant real-asset security tokens. It introduces the concept of partitions, where each `tokenId` represents a distinct partition with its own set of rights and privileges. This makes it suitable for various use cases, particularly semi-fungible asset management. The standard also includes features like token locking, forced transfers for recovery, address freezing, payouts, and dynamic compliance management using off-chain vouchers.",
  "title": "Dynamic Compliant Interop Security Token"
}